```

## 


```java
//
//
@SpringBootApplication(scanBasePackages="com.pjt") 

//
@SpringBootConfiguration
@EnableAutoConfiguration
@ComponentScan("com.pjt.boot") //
```

# 
## 
### 1. @Configuration
#### 

bootconfig.MyConfig,[PetUser](http://www.panjiangtao.cn/posts/spring3-1-pet-user/)
```java
@Configuration(proxyBeanMethods = true) //
public class MyConfig {

    @Bean //()user01id
        //
    public User user01(){
       return new User("zhangsan",18);
    }
    //
    // public User user01(){
    //     User zhangsan=new User("zhangsan",18);
    //     zhangsan.setPet(tomcatPet());
    //     return zhangsan;
    // }

    @Bean("Tom") //idTom
    public Pet tomcatPet(){
        return new Pet("tomcat");
    }
}
```

- 1. @Bean
- 2. 
- 3. proxyBeanMethodsbeantruefalse

#### 
```java
public class MainApplication {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        //1. ,
        Pet tom01 = run.getBean("Tom", Pet.class);
        Pet tom02 = run.getBean("Tom", Pet.class);
        System.out.println(""+(tom01==tom02));

        //2. bean
        MyConfig bean = run.getBean(MyConfig.class);
        System.out.println(bean);

        //3.1 proxyBeanMethodstrue
        User user = bean.user01();
        User user1 = bean.user01();
        System.out.println(user==user1);

        //3.2 proxyBeanMethodsfalse
        User user01 = run.getBean("user01", User.class);
        Pet Tom=run.getBean("Tom",Pet.class);
        System.out.println(":"+(user01.getPet()==Tom));
    }
}
```

### 2. @Import

```java
//@Import,
@Import({User.class, DBHelper.class})
```

### 3. @Conditional


```java
//@ConditionalOnMissingBean(name = "tom") //tom
public class MyConfig {

    @ConditionalOnBean(name="tom22") //tom,tom22user01
    @Bean
    public User user01(){
        User zhangsan = new User("zhangsan", 18);
        //userPet
        zhangsan.setPet(tomcatPet());
        return zhangsan;
    }

    @Bean("tom22")
    public Pet tomcatPet(){
        return new Pet("tomcat");
    }
}

```


```java
public static void main(String[] args) {
        //IOC
        ConfigurableApplicationContext run = SpringApplication.run(MainApplication.class, args);

        boolean tom = run.containsBean("tom");
        System.out.println("Tom"+tom);

        boolean user01 = run.containsBean("user01");
        System.out.println("user01"+user01);

        boolean tom22 = run.containsBean("tom22");
        System.out.println("tom22"+tom22);
    }
```

### 4. @ImportResource
xml:

```xml
    <bean id="haha" class="com.pjt.boot.bean.User">
        <property name="name" value="zhangsan"></property>
        <property name="age" value="18"></property>
    </bean>

    <bean id="hehe" class="com.pjt.boot.bean.Pet">
        <property name="name" value="tomcat"></property>
    </bean>
```

xml:

```java
@ImportResource("classpath:beans.xml")
public class MyConfig {
}
```

### 5.
JavapropertiesJavaBean

#### 1@ConfigurationProperties

```java
@Component  //
@ConfigurationProperties(prefix = "mycar")  //
public class Car{
    private String brand;
    private Integer price;

}
```
application.properties
```js
mycar.brand=BMW
mycar.price=100
```

#### 2@EnableConfigurationProperties
@ComponentEnableConfigurationProperties


```java
@EnableConfigurationProperties(Car.class)
//1Car
//2Car
public class MyConfig{
}
```
{% note warning %}
1@ConfigurationProperties(prefix = "mycar")
{% endnote %}

#### 3@EnableConfigurationProperties

